This paper is about evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of fitness-level partitions and transition probabilities, which are concepts related to data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of mutation rates, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
